# data-testid Convention

## Pattern

```
data-testid="domain.component.element-type"
```

All three segments are **required**. Use kebab-case within each segment. Separate segments with `.`.

| Segment | Description | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `domain` | Feature area or route domain | `auth`, `nav`, `bands`, `albums`, `pedals`, `account` |
| `component` | The specific view or form within that domain | `login-form`, `header`, `list`, `detail`, `add-form`, `edit-form` |
| `element-type` | What the element is and/or does | `email-input`, `submit-btn`, `table`, `error-message`, `back-link` |

## Rules

- **Stable**: never derived from dynamic content (no IDs, slugs, indices, user-generated strings)
- **Unique**: the full three-part string must be unique within the domain
- **Consistent element suffixes**: use `‚Äëbtn` for buttons, `‚Äëinput` for text/number/date inputs, `‚Äëselect` for dropdowns, `‚Äëtable` for tables, `‚Äëlink` for navigation anchors, `‚Äëmessage` for inline feedback, `‚Äëdialog` for modals
- **Pug syntax**: write as an attribute in parentheses ‚Äî `input(data-testid="auth.login-form.email-input")`
- **No dynamic values**: never interpolate server-side variables into a testid ‚Äî the rendered DOM value must be a static string
- **Exception ‚Äî structural mode discrimination**: a shared mixin may use Pug interpolation to switch between two fixed testid prefixes (e.g. `pedals.add-form` vs `pedals.edit-form`) when the mode is passed as a literal string by the caller and never derived from user data. Document the intent with an inline comment.

## Examples (Pug syntax)

```pug
//- Auth
input(data-testid="auth.login-form.email-input")
button(data-testid="auth.login-form.sign-in-btn")
span(data-testid="auth.login-form.error-message")

//- Navigation
a(data-testid="nav.header.bands-link") Bands
a(data-testid="nav.header.logout-btn") Logout

//- Pedals list
.pedals(data-testid="pedals.list.container")
a(data-testid="pedals.list.add-link") Add Pedal

//- Pedal admin form
input(data-testid="pedals.add-form.name-input")
button(data-testid="pedals.add-form.submit-btn")
```

## In Page Object Models (Playwright)

Reference test IDs using the full dot-notation string:

```ts
this.emailInput = page.getByTestId('auth.login-form.email-input')
this.submitButton = page.getByTestId('auth.login-form.sign-in-btn')
```

## Do Not

- Use the old flat kebab-case format: ~~`data-testid="email-input"`~~
- Embed dynamic values: ~~`data-testid="pedal-#{pedal.id}-delete-btn"`~~
- Interpolate server variables: ~~`data-testid="band-#{band.slug}"`~~
- Omit any of the three segments: ~~`data-testid="login.email-input"`~~
- Use underscores or camelCase: ~~`data-testid="auth.loginForm.emailInput"`~~

